														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1206695">
									

<p>I have read it (one of my favorite authors, in fact). The premise - a flip or change in perception that causes one to view beautiful things as ugly and vice versa, likely came from Phoenix, as Osamu Tezuka is a bit revered over here among the kind of people who draw comics for a living. While Phoenix plays the premise for tragedy and to show how pitiful a character had become, Saya no Uta and Franken Fran use the premise as a baseline for horror, both physical and psychological. What would a monster look like to someone with a flipped perspective, and how would they interact?</p>
<p>fuck i'm rambling about comic books jesus</p>
<p>Anyway, yes, SCP-750 was influenced by a number of those stories, Franken Fran and Saya no Uta among them.</p>

